I am up in the Eastern Sierras, creating epic art, when I mindlessly checked my tiktok, only to realize I had several warnings and then got logged out. I panicked and tried to log in only to find my 7th account permanent banned. 

I took a moment to grieve all of the moments I had posted, but couldn’t take long because I needed to shoot. As traipsed barefoot on these monumental rocks, I posed under heavenly rococo clouds. I posed and let a spell of energy up into the fiery red hellish hued sky. I ran to the furthest ridge and looked beyond as far as I could see using my movement to conjure my feelings and emote them to the wide spread sun rays above me.

I lost a piece of my internet reality, but when I look around at my physical life, I would forgo all 11k followers for these moments right here. 

RIP 🕊️

My account was taken down, now it’s back. The Gobline Show has been renewed for another season. All Hail. 💕

When my account randomly was suspended a day ago and then permanently deleted this morning ( before a very very flowery plea for appeal ), I had already come to terms with its loss. With all the art, videos, comments, messages, FUCKING BOOKING info gone, but leaving it all wasn’t the hard part. I was unsure how to move forward, where to put my time and energy and how much of a social influence I really need. It made me take a hard look about why I am on here and what I want to express. I love creation of all types. I love sharing and I especially love the community that surrounds me. I don’t care about numbers, about going viral ( even though let’s be real, dopamine hits are funnnn). I care about sinking deeper into my creations and exploring worlds I never knew existed in my physical life. Social media has been crucial to my success, but I realized I have so many people I can find even without socials now, that I have made a life that I love and people who will also find me wherever I go.

With that being said, I am going to work on a Newsletter so get ready to submit your emails lolllllllll

Welp. I strained my back muscle in yoga today while trying to do an inversion then falling over smack dab on the corner of a block. I literally couldn’t move for 30 min because of sharp needle like shooting pain and now can’t stand up straight. Yoga freak accident. 

A few days before this, I lounged soooo hard and neglected responsibilities, took advantage of my time like I had alllll the time in the world, frittered it away for nothing and now that I am physically unable to do the smallest tasks I am SO SAD I didn’t live up my able bodied days. I know I will heal, but there’s nothing like an injury to make you so so so grateful for your health. 

Now I am laid out on my velvet green couch like a hobbling goblin hag, but yesterday I was really hot so let’s all revel in that. Send your goblin good energy to my back please 🥲☹️

This is me now. My back injury is pretty severe so I’m going to stay put in bed and heal. In the meantime, please go out and move for me. Take a walk and smell the flowers. Clean your house. Wash your hair. Do all the things I can’t do right now and appreciate them. 

📸 @margot_tenenbaum______

Life Update: I fractured my L4 and L3 transverse process after doing a forearm stand in yoga and falling over onto my back on to the corner of a cork block. It’s not because of age/strength or previous injuries. It was a bizarre situation and injury that has put my whole life on pause. 

I got x-rays and a ct scan, but can’t do an mri because I can’t lay on my back. I have excruciating nerve pain in my back if I try to straighten it and the nerve hits mostly when I try to walk and takes me to the ground. 

I am going to bed rest. I can’t think of much else but my day to day since every step to the kitchen or bathroom is a feat. I am very tired, I am sad, and this time I am honestly a little scared the nerve pain won’t go away. 

Just wanted to post this for all the questions. 

📸 @dreselge
